police officer joe gallagher said two employees of rapid armor had stopped for breakfast and left a third guard in the back of the truck
gallagher said a man carrying a gun entered the back of the truck and handcuffed the guard. another man got into the truck and drove it away
according to witnesses, police said, the men later stopped the truck and fled in a van, taking with them bags containing $1 million
authorities said they did not know how the holdup man got into the back of the truck
about 100 firefighters from western states were sent to the smoky mountains of eastern tennessee today to fight fires which have broken out there, authorities said
fires, abetted by strong shifting winds and dry weather, have burned more than 1,300 acres in tennessee since wednesday. five separate fires were burning today
even if it does rain it will probably be less than an inch,'' said wilma marine, a spokeswoman at cherokee national forest, where a 300-acre fire had been contained
the u.s. forest service crews of about 200 firefighters from colorado, new mexico and arizona arrived thursday
the largest blaze in the great smoky mountains national park has grown to 500-plus acres about two miles west of chilhowee lake
a colony of red cockaded woodpeckers, an endangered species, was threatened by that fire, said misty seagle, a clerk in the park superintendent's office
no homes have been damaged by any of the fires
