general electric corp., in its quest for roper corp., said today it will move to michigan its legal battle challenging the appliance and garden equipment maker's agreement to be acquired by whirlpool corp
separately, roper said its board will meet next week to review bids from ge and whirlpool. ge increased its tender offer for roper on monday to $507 million, topping whirlpool's $470 million merger agreement with roper
the ge tender offer amounts to $54 a share; whirlpool's tender offer amounts to $50 a share for the augusta, ga.-based company
a federal judge here denied ge's request to move a lawsuit filed by whirlpool to delaware, where ge filed two suits challenging the roper-whirlpool combination
it was simply a matter of whether it would be consolidated in delaware or michigan,'' ge spokesman george jameson said
ge said today it will withdraw the federal court actions it filed in delaware in and refile them in the kalamazoo court, jameson said from ge headquarters in fairfield, conn
whirlpool will be inconvenienced by litigating in delaware, while ge will be inconvenienced by litigating in michigan,'' u.s. district judge richard a. enslen said in a written order issued thursday
but in ordering the case to be heard in michigan, enslen noted that many of the main witnesses are in michigan
whirlpool, headquartered in benton harbor, mich., has not said whether it will top ge's latest bid. ``we don't have a comment on that at this point,'' spokeswoman donna mclean said today
analysts have said that merging with roper would move whirlpool ahead of ge as the country's top appliance maker
whirlpool's suit charged that ge's initial $45-a-share offer for roper, made on march 6, was an attempt to sabotage a whirlpool-roper merger agreement announced in february in which whirlpool said it would pay $37.50 a share
whirlpool later sweetened its bid to $50 a share, and roper's board recommended shareholders accept the offer
in its lawsuits, ge claimed both whirlpool and roper failed to adequately disclose terms of their merger agreement under securities and exchange commission laws
the suit also claims whirlpool and roper failed to publicly disclose ge's prior interest in acquiring roper and accuses the roper board of concealing from shareholders that ge, as well as whirlpool, wanted to buy the company
share prices closed lower friday but finished well above their worst levels of the day reached after the release of disappointing british trade figures for february
the financial times-stock exchange 100-share index fell 14.8 points, or 0.8 percent, to close at 1,767.9
the index moved down as much as 23.3 points on the trade news but then recovered gradually through the afternoon as trading volume slackened considerably
