shares traded narrowly in the morning but then plunged when the government reported at 11:30 a.m. local time that britain's february merchandise trade deficit narrowed to 1.3 billion pounds, about $2.4 billion, from 1.4 billion pounds in january
the current account deficit, which includes invisible trade like financial services, narrowed to 720 million pounds, or $1.3 billion, from 844 million pounds, the department of trade and industry said
despite the narrowings, both deficits were much larger than the markets had expected
the sharp drop attracted a few bargain hunters. share prices recovered further on the back of markups by market makers after wall street opened, apparently in no mood to reenact thursday's sharp sell-off. but afternoon trading volume slowed to a trickle ahead of the weekend
